        public CityMap getCityMap(java.io.File xmlFile)
                   throws java.io.IOException,
                          ParserException
        Returns the cityMap described by the file given in parameter. This file must be at the xml format, and follow the correct syntax. If not, an exception will be thrown.
        Parameters:
        xmlFile - The file containing the xml description of the city map.
        Returns:
        The city map described by the xml file.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If the file is not reachable by the application.
        ParserException - If the file is not syntactically of meaningfully correct

      • getDeliveryRequest

        public DeliveryRequest getDeliveryRequest(java.io.File xmlFile,
                                          CityMap cityMap)
                                   throws java.io.IOException,
                                          ParserException
        Returns the delivery request described by the xml file provided in parameter. This file must be at the format xml and respect the right syntax.
        Parameters:
        xmlFile - The file describing the returned delivery request.
        cityMap - The city map on which the delivery request will be applied.
        Returns:
        The delivery request described by the xmlFile.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If the file is not reachable by the application.
        ParserException - If the xmlFile does not respect the right syntax.
